The answer is simple, there is a lack of competition that really makes a fight.
Maybe it sounds paradox, in Czech Republic there are three mobile networks and a penetration of far more than 100%.
On the other hand, mobile providers are pleased to say that there is extremely much competition on the Czech market.
The President of the Czech Telecommunications Authority (ČTU) Pavel Dvořák, who in the past often said that there was no room for another provider in Czech Republic.
