However, there is another option - a virtual provider.
Just the entry of virtual providers to the mobile market brought a significant price reduction, which then also had to respond to the classic mobile providers.
There were still similar votes on the market in Britain before companies such as Tesco Mobile or Virgin Mobile arrived in the UK as in Czech Republic.
However, it has been shown that there is space for such providers and that they can really be successful.
On the other hand, you do not need to look for examples for a long time.
In February this we reported about the start of the virtual provider Mobilking in Poland.
In only half a year, this provider managed to win more than 100 thousand customers and thus rise to the five-largest supplier of the country.
At the back of Mobilking, the Penta Finance Group, which has in the Czech Republic, among other things, U:phone.
The advantage of virtual providers is to focus on a much more specific target group.
